"card"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/AI-Article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s native keyboard APIs lack many features that are needed to build AI-based keyboards, for instance to read an entire document to be able to perform tasks like spellchecking and proofreading, or to let users type text within the keyboard extension."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"👑 KeyboardKit Pro unlocks many AI-enabling capabilities, like making it possible to read the full document and type directly within the keyboard. You can sign up for KeyboardKit Pro from the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/keyboardkit.com","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"anchor":"Full-Document-Reader","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Full Document Reader"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s native text document proxy doesn’t return all the text within the document. It cuts off the available text at any time, e.g. at the previous or next paragraph, which makes it hard to provide AI-based features that require more context."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro therefore unlocks "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/UIKit\/UITextDocumentProxy\/fullDocumentContext(config:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proxy extensions that let you read "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}]},{"type":"text","text":" text from the proxy:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let proxy = keyboardContext.textDocumentProxy","let result = try await proxy.fullDocumentContext()"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This will provide you with all the text before and after the input cursor, as well as an aggregate of all the available text in the document.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Proxy-Article","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" article for more information.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Next-Word-Prediction","level":2,"text":"Next Word Prediction","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple’s native text prediction utilities stopped supporting next word prediction in iOS 16. It instead only provides predictions on already typed text, without any (known) way to get next word predictions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro therefore unlocks ways to perform next word prediction via 3rd party AI services. The easiest way to enable next word prediction, is to add a Claude- or OpenAI-based ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Autocomplete\/RemotePredictionRequest","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" to your ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardApp","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension KeyboardApp {","","    static var keyboardKitDemo: KeyboardApp {","        KeyboardApp(","            ...","            autocomplete: .init(","                nextWordPredictionRequest: .claude(apiKey: \"your-key-here\")","            )","        )","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Users can then enable "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/AutocompleteSettings\/isNextWordPredictionEnabled","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to allow "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Autocomplete\/StandardAutocompleteService","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to perform predictions. You can also use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/AutocompleteSettings\/nextWordPredictionRequestType","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" setting for runtime customizations, or customize the service with code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Autocomplete-Article","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" article for more information and important considerations."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Text-Input","text":"Text Input","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s native input controller & text document proxy don’t let you type in text fields within the keyboard. Instead, text will be sent to the main app even if a text field in the keyboard is focused. This makes it hard to let user perform AI-based prompting within the keyboard."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro therefore unlocks a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardTextField"},{"type":"text","text":" that automatically manages in-keyboard typing, without any extra code:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["extension MyView: View {","","    @EnvironmentObject var context: KeyboardContext","","    @State var text = \"\"","","    var body: some View {","        KeyboardTextField(","            text: $text, ","            keyboardContext: context","        )","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The ke